Adjust rack to upper position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Place @butter{3%tablespoon} in a #small bowl{} and bring to room temperature.

> Alternatively, microwave butter in bowl until softened, about 15 seconds.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{24%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Pick @rosemary{2%tablespoon}(leaves picked and minced) from stems; mince leaves. (Save remaining rosemary sprigs for later.) Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, minced rosemary, half the garlic, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast until browned and tender, about ~{30%minutes} (we'll add more to the sheet halfway through). Meanwhile, zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Squeeze 2 TBSP lemon juice into another #small bowl{}. Stir lemon zest into bowl with softened butter.

Pat @chicken breasts{24%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #plate{}. Meanwhile, use a #heavy-bottomed pan{} or #mallet{} to pound @black peppercorns{2%tablespoon} in their bag until coarsely ground.

Once potatoes have roasted 15 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven and push potatoes to one side. Add @green beans{12%ounce} and whole rosemary sprigs to empty side. Toss green beans with @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Return to oven and roast until veggies are browned and tender, about ~{15%minutes} more.

Add crushed peppercorns and remaining garlic to pan used to cook chicken. Cook on medium-high until lightly browned, about ~{30%seconds}. Add @chicken stock concentrate{2}, reserved 2 TBSP lemon juice, and @water{1/2%cup}. Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to medium and stir in @sour cream{4%tablespoon}. Cook until sauce is creamy, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Stir in lemon butter.

Divide potatoes, green beans, and chicken among plates. Top chicken with pan sauce. Serve with any remaining lemon quarters on the side for squeezing over.

> This creamy peppercorn pan sauce spooned over the juicy chicken and roasted vegetables is a winter dream.